\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 4. The Complete Production Layer Stack Order\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Now that we have every single layer mechanics mapped out\'97from the distant scrolling sky to the foreground pillars\'97here is the exact sequence your Python script will use to composite each frame from back to front:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading40\partightenfactor0

\f4\i\fs28\fsmilli14118 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 # 1. Start with the moving parallax sky frame as your bottom canvas layer
\f5\i0 \
frame_canvas = render_parallax_sky(cycle_frame)\
\

\f4\i # 2. Layer the Architectural Shell over the sky
\f5\i0 \

\f4\i # (Skylights and outdoor sky are transparent holes, revealing the moving sky behind them)
\f5\i0 \
frame_canvas.alpha_composite(mall_architectural_shell)\
\

\f4\i # 3. Inject active advertiser assets into the storefront wall slots
\f5\i0 \
frame_canvas.alpha_composite(ad_1, dest=(350, 500))\
frame_canvas.alpha_composite(ad_2, dest=(1120, 500))\
\

\f4\i # 4. Overlap the security guard sprite at his dynamic walking path position
\f5\i0 \
frame_canvas.alpha_composite(current_guard_sprite, dest=(guard_x, guard_y))\
\

\f4\i # 5. Apply advanced environmental lighting masks (skylight sunbeams / streetlights / flashlights)
\f5\i0 \
frame_canvas = apply_advanced_environmental_lighting(frame_canvas, cycle_frame, TOTAL_FRAMES, guard_x)\
\

\f4\i # 6. Overlay the foreground columns and lamp posts over everything to finalize depth
\f5\i0 \
frame_canvas.alpha_composite(foreground_pillars, dest=(0, 0))\
\

\f4\i # 7. Render text layers (Music HUD metadata and occasional dialogue bubbles)
\f5\i0 \
frame_canvas = render_text_layers(frame_canvas, guard_x, guard_y, frame, TRACK_FRAME_MAP, AUDIO_LOOP_DURATION)\
